# Commit Message Format

Use Conventional Commits with explicit monorepo scope:

`type(scope): summary`

- `type` must be one of: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `docs`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`
- `scope` should identify the touched package/app/domain (for example: `lo-star`, `lotato`, `meshcore`, `meshtastic`, `potato-mesh`, `repo`)
- `summary` should be imperative, lower-case, and concise
- the full subject line (`type(scope): summary`) must be at most 50 characters

## Monorepo Scope Rules

- Single package change: use one concrete scope, e.g. `fix(lo-star): ...`
- Cross-package change: use a shared domain scope, e.g. `feat(mesh): ...` or `chore(repo): ...`
- Avoid empty scope unless the change truly spans the whole repo

## Examples

- `feat(lotato): add ingest retry backoff`
- `fix(lo-star): make lofs rename safe on spiffs`
- `refactor(meshcore): simplify wifi cli handlers`
- `chore(repo): align platformio flags across variants`

